# Hoist framer-motion to the top-level node_modules so Vite can resolve
# `motion/react`'s `export * from 'framer-motion'` re-export chain.
#
# `motion` (the rebranded package) is our single direct dep. Internally
# its `react.mjs` is just `export * from 'framer-motion'` — the actual
# implementation lives in framer-motion as a transitive dep. Without
# this hoist, pnpm keeps framer-motion isolated under
# `node_modules/.pnpm/...` and Vite's optimizeDeps walker (which
# resolves bare specifiers from the project root) can't find it.
#
# This is purely a resolver hint — package.json still lists only
# `motion`, so there's no duplicated dependency entry.
public-hoist-pattern[]=framer-motion
